- Merged example usage docs with [I2K tutorial docs](https://github.com/basedrhys/I2K-Tutorial)
- Add unit tests for recently added class

name: WekaDeeplearning4j v1.7.0
body:
# Changelog

- Introduce the new Dl4jCNNExplorer class ([usage examples](https://deeplearning.cms.waikato.ac.nz/examples/dl4j-inference/)), which allows you to use zoo models or custom trained models to perform prediction on an individual image, without loading a `.arff` dataset.
- Implement the ScoreCAM saliency map generation method and integrate it with the Dl4jCNNExplorer ([usage examples](https://deeplearning.cms.waikato.ac.nz/examples/dl4j-inference/#example-4-saliency-map-generation)).
- Implement a progress bar (for command line and GUI) to aid usability with long-running tasks.

name: wekaDeeplearning4j-v1.6.0
body:
This release primarily focuses on improvements and new features for the image-classification side of WekaDeeplearning4j.

# Changelog
- **Pretrained Models** - Add DL4J and Keras pre-trained models into the [model zoo](https://deeplearning.cms.waikato.ac.nz/user-guide/model-zoo/). WekaDeeplearning4j now has over 30 pre-trained models, including big names like ResNet, InceptionV3, and EfficientNet
- **Improved Feature Extraction** - Enable `Dl4jMlpFilter` to use a pre-trained model as feature extractor, as well as use multiple feature layers, and different pooling methods
- Add new usage examples for [feature extraction](https://deeplearning.cms.waikato.ac.nz/examples/featurize-mnist/) and [training](https://deeplearning.cms.waikato.ac.nz/examples/classifying-your-own/) with a pre-trained model
- Add `ImageDirectoryLoader` - an easy way to load 'folder-organised' image datasets into WEKA ([usage example](https://deeplearning.cms.waikato.ac.nz/examples/classifying-your-own/#creating-the-meta-arff-file-imagedirectoryloader))
- Update Deeplearning4j backend to `1.0.0-beta7`
- Add CUDA 10.2 support
- Drop CUDA 9.2 support

## Changelog
- Update Deeplearning4j to `1.0.0-beta`
- Remove `GoogLeNet` (support was dropped in Deeplearning4j)
- Fix de/serialization
- Rewrite buildscript in python
- Replace `kernselSizeX/Y`, `strideX/Y`, `paddingX/Y` with `row/column`

- Add `WeightNoise`
- Add `FlatToRelational` filter
- Add `Dropout` implementations
- Add `Schedule`s for parameters
- Add more `Distribution` implementaitons
- Add `LocalResponseNormalizationLayer`
- Add `DropoutLayer`
- Add iterator for ARFF datasets with relational sequence attributes: `RelationalInstanceIterator`
- Add CUDA 9.0 and 9.1 support
- Add installation scripts for cuda libraries for linux/macosx and windows

## Package Structure
Starting with version 1.5.0, the GPU libraries are to be installed via the `install-cuda-libs` scripts. Further instructions can be found in the [documentation](https://deeplearning.cms.waikato.ac.nz/install#add-gpu-support).

## Changelog

This release focuses mainly on adding text classification and regression capabilities, introducing a new classifier and adding new iterators to handle text data accordingly using word embedding. - Add new iterators for text data (docs):

name: wekaDeeplearning4j-v1.3.1
body:
## Changes
- Choosing a zoo model now adds its layers to the current configuration. It is also possible to change the layer setup and parameters (keep in mind, that this will reset the `zooModel` option to `CustomNet` since the changed setup does not comply with the actually chosen zoo model anymore) 
- Add warning if validation set in EarlyStopping was too small
- Add global information to different options in the GUI
- Add more warnings if invalid setups which configuring the network
- Fix log file if `WEKA_HOME` was not set
- Add layer configuration validation
- Add option for evaluation after `N` epochs to `EpochListener`
- Reduce evaluation time

### Update
This version suffered from a memory bug which is fixed in `v1.3.2` and above.

name: wekaDeeplearning4j-v1.3.0
body:
## Changes
- Update documentation
- Use IUpdater backend
- Remove per-layer parameters
- Introduce EarlyStopping condition (see the [documentation](https://deeplearning.cms.waikato.ac.nz/getting-started/#early-stopping))
- Use `$WEKA_HOME/network.log` as default logging file
- Fix loading images for directories with spaces
- Logs now show metrics for training and validation set by default if EarlyStopping is enabled

### Attention
This version is not compatible with configurations of earlier versions (< 1.3.0) due to the removal of many parameters in the layer configuration. These parameters are now in the `NeuralNetConfiguration`. Furthermore, the `Updater` parameters have been moved to the updater-editor. These changes make the use of many parameters more clear.

### Update
Downloads removed due to a bug. Please use `v1.3.1` or later.
